    "Reason : 1 - The proposed upper floor flat, by virtue of its design and layout fails to achieve a high quality, comfortable and functional standard of residential accommodation for future occupiers, failing to meet minimum space standards for new dwellings (Gross Internal Area and amenity space standards), contrary to Planning Policy CS14 (Design) of Merton's Core Planning Strategy (2011), Policy DM D2 (Design considerations in all development) of Merton's Sites and Policies Plan 2014, Policy D6 (Housing quality and standards) of the London Plan 2021 and Technical Housing Standards - nationally described space standard (2015).",
    "Reason : 2 - In the absence of an Air Quality Neutral Statement, the applicant has failed to demonstrate the scheme would be air quality neutral and not result in a detrimental impact to air quality. The proposals are contrary to, in particular, policy S1 of the London Plan 2021."
